<a name="announcements">
<center><h2><a href="#top">Announcements</a></h2></center>
</a></a>

<UL>
<a name="software">
<LI><font size=-1><em>(11/14/96)</em></font> <B>A pre-release version of the new CODE is now available (and it's FREE)! </B> Click <a href="http://www.cs.utexas.edu/users/code/License.html">here</a> to download the software.
<p>
This is a major new revision of CODE (click here for <a href="http://www.cs.utexas.edu/users/code/code2.1b1-screenshot.gif">a screen shot</A>). It features a sophisticated new user-interface which provides many improvements to the previous version of CODE, making it easier and more pleasant to use. Some of the features include a Mac-like interface (<i>&agrave; la</i> MacDraw), multiple windows for subgraph editing, a hierarchy browser and more.</LI>

<P>

<LI><font size=-1><em>(10/8/96)</em></font> <B>Article on CODE:</b> <a href="http://hpcwire.com/hpcwire.html">HPCwire</a>, the on-line journal of high-performance computing, recently published an article on CODE entitled <a href="http://www.cs.utexas.edu/users/code/CODE-HPCwire-article.html"><em>"Visual Parallel Programming May Come of Age with CODE"</em></a> that they've been kind enough to let us reproduce here.
<p>
<p>

